el makers more fine-grained control over how this...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/30/1136721/this-startups-new-mechanistic-interpretability-tool-lets-you-debug-llms/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 8}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34946", "title": "Anthropic's new benchmark claims Claude can match human experts in bioinformatics", "summary": "With BioMysteryBench, Anthropic wants to show that Claude can solve real bioinformatics problems at an expert level. The results are promising, but come with important caveats.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/anthropics-new-benchmark-claims-claude-can-match-human-experts-in-bioinformatics/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 6}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136684", "title": "Exclusive eBook: Inside the stealthy startup that pitched brainless human clones", "summary": "The ultimate plan to live forever is a brand new body. This subscriber-only eBook explores R3 Bio, a small startup that has pitched a startling and ethically charged vision for &#8220;brainless clones&#8221; to serve the role of backup human bodies. by Antonio Regalado March 20, 2026 Related Stories...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/30/1136684/exclusive-ebook-inside-the-stealthy-startup-that-pitched-brainless-human-clones/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 5}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34957", "title": "OpenAI says it hit its 10 gigawatt compute goal years ahead of schedule", "summary": "OpenAI says it has reached its goal of 10 gigawatts of AI compute capacity in the United States several years ahead of schedule.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/openai-says-it-hit-its-10-gigawatt-compute-goal-years-ahead-of-schedule/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 4}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136713", "title": "The Download: the North Pole\u2019s future and humanoid data", "summary": "This is today&#8217;s edition of The Download, our weekday newsletter that provides a daily dose of what&#8217;s going on in the world of technology. Digging for clues about the North Pole\u2019s past In the past, getting to the North Pole involved a treacherous trip through ice many meters thick. But la...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/30/1136713/the-download-north-pole-future-humanoid-data/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 3}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34969", "title": "Tencent's 440 MB AI model translates 33 languages offline on your phone", "summary": "Tencent has released a compact AI translation model as an open-weight model that it claims outperforms Google Translate and runs completely offline on smartphones.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/tencents-440-mb-ai-model-translates-33-languages-offline-on-your-phone/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34958", "title": "Google CEO says Pichai says people \"love\" AI Overviews and keep coming back to search more", "summary": "Alphabet is investing up to $190 billion in AI and cloud infrastructure through 2026, and the company says spending will rise \"significantly\" again in 2027.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/google-ceo-says-pichai-says-people-love-ai-overviews-and-keep-coming-back-to-search-more/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 1}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34988", "title": "Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella says AI success is \"more about getting intense users and intense usage\" than seat counts", "summary": "Microsoft is posting record profits and strong cloud growth, but just like Google, the company is saying little about how its generative AI business is actually performing.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/microsoft-ceo-satya-nadella-says-ai-success-is-more-about-getting-intense-users-and-intense-usage-than-seat-counts/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 0}], "today_tech