calize across frequency ranges that differ substantially from humans, often extending into the ultrasonic domain. Yet most computational bioacoustics systems rely on audio models pre-trained at 16 kHz, restricting their usable bandwidth to the 0-8 kHz baseband and discar...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.27936", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.27936v1/2604.27936v1/x1.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.27122v1", "title": "InterPartAbility: Text-Guided Part Matching for Interpretable Person Re-Identification", "summary": "Abstract: Text-to-image person re-identification (TI-ReID) relies on natural-language text description to retrieve top matching individuals from a large gallery of images. While recent large vision-language models (VLMs) achieve strong retrieval performance, their decisions remain largely uninterpre...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.27122", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.27122v1/2604.27122v1/x1.png", "score": 9}]}